  <md:abstract><list>
<item>Define antinode, node, fundamental, overtones, and harmonics.</item>
<item>Identify instances of sound interference in everyday situations.</item>
<item>Describe how sound interference occurring inside open and closed tubes changes the characteristics of the sound, and how this applies to sounds produced by musical instruments.</item>
<item>Calculate the length of a tube using sound wave measurements.</item>
</list></md:abstract>
